Dihedral
private class Dihedral.Simple3DVector

Trivial implementation of a vector in 3D space. The implementation is far from being complete, as only very few methods are introduced.

crossProd

public Dihedral.Simple3DVector crossProd(Dihedral.Simple3DVector v)
Calculates and returns the cross product of two vectors. Object this is multiplied by the vector v. Note, that unlike dotProd() cross product is not symmetrical.
A new instance is created and returned, object this is not modified.

Parameters:
v - right side operand of cross product
Returns:
cross product vector this x v
